The paper deals with efficient evaluation of cosine threshold queries, which are commonly used in information retrieval (IR) and database (DB) applications. The paper also mentions applications in image search (CV) and mass spectrometry, which falls under the category of data structures (DS). The techniques developed in the paper are quite general and can be applied to a large class of similarity functions, which falls under the category of machine learning (LG). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.DS, cs.CV, and cs.LG.
